NTC thermistors can also be characterised with the "B" (or "β") parameter equation, which is essentially the Steinhart–Hart equation with formula_17, formula_18 and formula_19,
Where the temperatures are in kelvin and "R"0 is the resistance at temperature "T"0 (25 °C = 298.15 K). Solving for "R" yields:
